In the modern era of automation and robotics, autonomous vehicles are a focus of research in business and education.
With the ever increasing number of unmanned aerial vehicles in various activities, there is an increased need for autonomy in these systems too.
Due to rules set by the government, road-tracking navigation is garnering interest.
we propose an automated solution to driving through city streets by learning from a skilled driver, a data-driven solution
Derived from the classic image classification algorithms, our classifier is built to detect roads using the tomographic reconstructions of the input frames.
